<p>if (m_simulateGravity) {<br>
xdot = xdot.plus(VecBuilder.fill(0, -9.8));<br>
}</p>
<p>My first thought for fixing this is to multiply 9.8 by the cosine of the elevators angle to figure out the real acceleration of the system. Would this work?</p>
<p>if (m_simulateGravity) {<br>
xdot = xdot.plus(VecBuilder.fill(0, -9.8 * Math.cos(elevatorAngleRads)));<br>
}</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":2,"updated_at":"2024-10-29T21:49:46.144Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":13,"reads":225,"readers_count":224,"score":125.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":474000,"topic_slug":"simulating-elevator-at-an-angle","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62573,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3075 Code Lead"},"post_url":"/t/simulating-elevator-at-an-angle/474000/1","custom_user_title":"3075 Code Lead","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3441406,"name":"Anand Rajamani","username":"asid61","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/asid61/{size}/7179_2.png","created_at":"2024-10-29T22:12:58.038Z","cooked":"<p>I can’t think of a reason why that wouldn’t work, but I’m not too familiar with the rest of the sim classes. Multiplying by cosine of angle is the same way that arm kG works.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":2,"updated_at":"2024-10-29T22:13:42.728Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":197,"readers_count":196,"score":54.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":474000,"topic_slug":"simulating-elevator-at-an-angle","display_username":"Anand Rajamani","primary_group_na